Love Nando's but had a poor experience last night at this location (first time eating here specifically). My girlfriend and I both each ordered the chicken skewers with sides. Both of our skewers came in really cold. I let the hostess know and she apologized. She mentioned said that they "had a rush but that's still not an excuse for the food to come in cold." Fine, no big deal. She took our food away and we were sitting there for nearly half an hour before I went up to another hostess (the one I originally spoke to was no where to be found) and mentioned that we were still waiting. She went to the kitchen and I guess this wasn't communicated to anyone because they had not started our new order. The manager and one of the cooks came over and apologized and offered us some fries and an extra skewer - which was nice. However, their excuse for the miscommunication was because they had a "rush". So our food was cold the first time because of a rush and then we didn't get served again because there was a rush? Not a great first impression at this location. Love Nando's but probably won't come back to this particular one again.

I will start this off by saying I do not really like chicken. My family, however, LOVES chicken. So we ended up at Nando's and my Hope's were not high that I would find something to eat. I was mistaken.  Nando's has to be one of my favorite places to eat right now. Even the chicken. It is juicy and delicious with a hint of kick that it strong enough for me to notice but not so strong that my kids won't eat it. The fries are delicious. The portabella and halloumi wrap (though I get it on the portugese roll) is amazing with the mango lime marinade as well. My favorite dish.  Oh and of course...there's the bottomless sole whip. And it is delicious. And bottomless. And the experience always transports me out of cold Chicago to somewhere warm and sunny for a little while.  They are family friendly, but not offensively so like some places. They have kids menus, crayons, high chairs, and an awesome family bathroom without pulling the changer from the regular bathrooms. (Which, might I add, are very clean and nice. My only bathroom complaint was it was kinda cold in there. ;p)  We always feel welcome and leave happy when we visit Nando's. I highly recommend it. Get yourself a bottle of the perinaise for the road too. It goes great on everything from holiday cracker plates to quesadillas to adding some spice to a sandwich.  Ooh, I wonder how it would be in deviled eggs...mmmm...I bet it is good there too!  Either way, go there. Enjoy yourself. Be happy.
